title: Let Them Theory - Important Caveats
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The "Let Them" rule has specific limits. You should '''NOT''' use it when:

* Someone is doing something '''dangerous''' or illegal.
* You witness '''discrimination''' or injustice.
* Your '''physical or emotional safety''' is being violated.

In these cases, the response is action and self-advocacy, not passive acceptance.